              >
                View Installation Guide
              </a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </FeatureSection>

        <!-- FAQ Section -->
        <FeatureSection id="faq" title="Frequently Asked Questions">
          <div class="space-y-6">
            <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6">
              <h4 class="font-semibold text-slate-900 mb-3">
                How do I migrate from Mailchimp to Notifuse?
              </h4>
              <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">
                Migration is straightforward: Export your contacts from
                Mailchimp as CSV, then import them into Notifuse using our CSV
                import tool with auto-detection. Recreate your email templates
                using the visual MJML builder, and connect your preferred email
                provider (Amazon SES, Mailgun, etc.). Check our <a
                  href="https://docs.notifuse.com"
                  class="text-primary hover:underline">documentation</a
                > for details.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6">
              <h4 class="font-semibold text-slate-900 mb-3">
                How much can I save switching from Mailchimp?
              </h4>
              <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">
                Notifuse is free software. With Amazon SES (~$0.10 per 1,000
                emails), sending 100,000 emails/month costs roughly $10 in
                provider fees plus a few dollars for hosting. Compare that to
                Mailchimp's Standard plan pricing at scale, plus $20 per block
                of 25,000 transactional emails if you use Mandrill.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6">
              <h4 class="font-semibold text-slate-900 mb-3">
                Does Notifuse have everything Mailchimp has?
              </h4>
              <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">
                No — and we're transparent about that. Mailchimp offers
                landing pages, SMS marketing, predictive analytics, 300+
                integrations, Send Time Optimization, and multivariate testing
                that Notifuse doesn't have. But Notifuse offers data
                ownership, email provider flexibility, multi-tenancy, included
                transactional email, and an open-source codebase that Mailchimp
                doesn't.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6">
              <h4 class="font-semibold text-slate-900 mb-3">
                Is Notifuse harder to set up than Mailchimp?
              </h4>
              <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">
                Notifuse requires self-hosting via Docker. If you're
                comfortable with Docker, setup takes minutes with our one-click
                deployment options (PikaPods, RepoCloud, Sealos). If you
                prefer zero infrastructure management, Mailchimp's managed
                service may be a better fit for your team.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6">
              <h4 class="font-semibold text-slate-900 mb-3">
                Can I use my existing email provider with Notifuse?
              </h4>
              <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">
                Yes. Notifuse integrates natively with Amazon SES, Mailgun,
                Postmark, SendGrid, Mailjet, SparkPost, and any SMTP server.
                You can even use different providers for different purposes —
                e.g., SES for bulk campaigns and Postmark for transactional
                email.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6">
              <h4 class="font-semibold text-slate-900 mb-3">
                Does Notifuse support SMS?
              </h4>
              <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">
                Not currently. Notifuse focuses on email marketing and
                transactional email. If SMS is critical for your business,
                Mailchimp offers it as a paid add-on in select regions (US,
                Canada, UK, EU, Australia).
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6">
              <h4 class="font-semibold text-slate-900 mb-3">
                Is there enterprise support available?
              </h4>
              <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">
                Yes! Notifuse offers enterprise support with priority
                assistance, custom implementation, training, onboarding, and
                SLA guarantees. Contact us for details.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </FeatureSection>

        <!-- Final CTA -->
        <section class="border-b border-gray-200">
          <div class="px-4 lg:px-8 py-20">
            <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
              <ComparisonCTA
                title="Ready to take control of your email?"
                description="Join developers and marketers who have switched from Mailchimp to Notifuse for full data ownership, provider flexibility, and no per-contact pricing."
              />
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>
      </ComparisonLayout>

      <!-- Footer -->
      <Footer />
    </div>
  </body>
</html>
